    <p>In principle, after the purpose of processing personal information is completed, USC shall destroy all personal information without due. The procedures, deadlines, and methods for destruction are as follows: - The information entered by user of the destruction procedures is transferred to a separate DB after achieving the purpose (separate documents in case of written form) and stored for a certain period of time or immediately destroyed in accordance with internal policies and other related laws. Personal information transferred to DB is not used for any other purpose except under the law. – If the personal information is destroyed, the user is not required within 5 working days from the end of the retention period, or if the personal information is unnecessary, such as achieving the purpose of processing the personal information, abolishing the service, or terminating the project. – Devastation Method: The information in electronic file type uses a technical method that prevents the record from being reused. </p>
    
    
